🧠 throw new Error() – Teaching Guide

👉 English: Used to manually create and throw an error.

1️⃣ Meaning (Tamil)

👉 throw = thooki podrathu
👉 Error = thappu / problem

So,

🧠
Neengale error create panni JS-kitta solrathu.

🔥 Simple Example
if(age < 18){
  throw new Error("Not Eligible")
}

Explain students-ku:

👉 Age 18-kum keezha irundhaa
👉 program stop
👉 error message kaatum.

2️⃣ Why use pannrom?

Teach this:

✔ Custom error create panna
✔ Wrong data stop panna
✔ Validation fail aagumbodhu
✔ API error handle panna

3️⃣ Must use with try / catch
try{
  throw new Error("Something wrong")
}catch(err){
  console.log(err.message)
}

Tamil:

👉 throw panninaa
👉 catch pidikkum.

4️⃣ Real Life Example 🧠

Teacher class-la:

Student homework pannala na:

🗣️
“ERROR! Homework missing!”

👉 Class stop 😄

5️⃣ Async/Await example
async function getData(){
 try{
  if(!email.includes("@")){
    throw new Error("Invalid Email")
  }
 }catch(err){
  console.log(err.message)
 }
}

🔑 One Line Teaching (board la):

Tamil:

👉 throw new Error = manually error create pannrathu.

English:

👉 Throw new Error is used to raise custom errors.

📋 Board Summary

throw

new Error()

custom message

try / catch

stops execution

✅ FINAL:

throw new Error() use panninaa:

✔ execution stop
✔ error message show
✔ catch block trigger

