🧠 if(!res.ok) – Full Explanation (Teaching Ready)

👉 English: Checks whether API response is successful.

1️⃣ res.ok na enna?

Tamil:

👉 Server correct-aa data kudutha
👉 res.ok = true

👉 Server problem / 404 / 500 vandhaa
👉 res.ok = false

Simple example:

Server success → ✅ true
Server fail → ❌ false

2️⃣ !res.ok na enna?

! = NOT

So:

!res.ok


Tamil:

👉 Response correct illa na

3️⃣ Why use pannrom?

Teach students like this:

🧠
fetch() error throw pannaathu.

Network fail mattum thaan catch pogum.

But API 404 / 500 vandhaalum
fetch success nu ninaikkum 😱

Athaan:

👉 neengale check pannanum.

🔥 Without res.ok
const res = await fetch(url)
const data = await res.json()


404 vandhaalum json try pannum → crash 😵

✅ With res.ok
if(!res.ok){
 throw new Error("Data Fetching Issue")
}


👉 Problem irundhaa:

✔ manual error
✔ catch block pogum
✔ app safe

🧠 Real Life Example

Food order pannunga:

Waiter vandhu sollran:

"Sorry sir, dish illa"

👉 neenga sapduveengala? NO 😄

Athaan res.ok

📋 Teaching Flow (board la)
API validation steps:

fetch API

check res.ok

if false → throw error

catch handle

🔑 One Line Teaching:

Tamil:

👉 res.ok = server success check.

English:

👉 res.ok verifies HTTP response status.

✅ FINAL ANSWER:

if(!res.ok) use pannrathu:

✔ server error catch panna
✔ json crash avoid panna
✔ proper error handling

