🧠 Topic Name
useEffect + IIFE

👉 English: Used to run async code inside useEffect.

🔥 STEP 1 — Problem Explain

Students-ku first idha kaamikkanum:

useEffect(async ()=>{
 const res = await fetch(url)
},[])


❌ WRONG ❌

Explain:

React allow pannaathu.

Because:

👉 useEffect callback async aaga koodaadhu.

STEP 2 — Solution

So inside oru async function create panni call pannanum.

Two ways:

✅ Method 1 — Named Function
useEffect(()=>{
 async function fetchData(){
   const res = await fetch(url)
 }
 fetchData()
},[])

✅ Method 2 — IIFE 🔥
useEffect(()=>{
 (async()=>{
   const res = await fetch(url)
 })()
},[])

🧠 IIFE na enna?

Tamil:

👉 Function create pannitu
👉 same line-la call pannrathu.

Example:
(()=> console.log("Hi"))()

🔥 Why IIFE use pannrom?

Teach students:

✔ async directly useEffect-la use panna mudiyathu
✔ Separate function create panna venam
✔ Short & clean code
✔ Immediate execution

🧠 Real Life Example

Fan switch on pannitu odane fan start.

Fan switch = function
Fan start = IIFE

📋 Board Summary
Flow:

useEffect runs

IIFE runs

async await works

API call

setState

🔑 One Line Teaching:

Tamil:

👉 useEffect-kulla async venumna IIFE use pannuvom.

English:

👉 IIFE allows async execution inside useEffect.

✅ FINAL ANSWER:

useEffect + IIFE use pannrathu:

✔ async allow panna
✔ code short panna
✔ immediate run panna


